    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Phaius tahitensis are hypertension, which is reduced by its antioxidant properties, and diabetes, whose symptoms are managed by the plant's anti-inflammatory effects. Inflammation is also alleviated by Phaius tahitensis, making it a potential treatment for various conditions such as arthritis, which benefits from its anti-inflammatory compounds. Anxiety is mitigated by the plant's anxiolytic properties, and asthma symptoms are improved by its ability to relax bronchial muscles. Additionally, Phaius tahitensis has been studied for its potential to prevent cancer cell growth and to treat digestive issues, such as gastritis, by reducing inflammation and promoting gut health. Its antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties also help to alleviate symptoms of cardiovascular disease, fever, urinary tract infections, anemia, and stress, as well as insomnia, eczema, rheumatism, depression, fatigue, and high blood pressure.",
