    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Phaius tahitensis are flavonoids, saponins, phenolic acids, phenylethanoid glycosides, and terpenoids, which have been identified as the primary bioactive compounds responsible for its medicinal properties. Phaius tahitensis contains various flavonoids such as rutin, kaempferol, and quercetin, which exhibit antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial activities. Saponins present in this plant have been reported to possess anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory effects, while phenolic acids like caffeic acid and ferulic acid display antioxidant and antimicrobial properties. Phenylethanoid glycosides, including acteoside and isoacteoside, have been found to exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, whereas terpenoids like limonene and pinene have been reported to possess antimicrobial and antioxidant properties. These bioactive compounds contribute to the medicinal properties of Phaius tahitensis, making it a valuable resource for the development of new therapeutic agents.",
